dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5020  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7: EM of immunoperoxidase labeled Girk2 (KCNJ6) showed both pre- and post-synaptic localization.\n\n\"Electron micrographs of the distal part of the stratum radiatum of the hippocampal CA1 region showing colocalization for Rgs7 or Gβ5 (GNB5) with Girk2 (KCNJ6), as detected using a pre-embedding immunogold method. Labelling is shown with immunogold for the Rgs7 or Gβ5, and with immunoperoxidase for the Girk2 subunit.\n\nPostsynaptically, Rgs7 (panel A) or Gβ5 (panel B) were seen in dendritic spines (s) of presumed pyramidal cells immunopositive for Girk2. Presynaptically, Rgs7 (panel C) or Gβ5 (panel D) were detected in Girk2-positive axon terminal (at) establishing asymmetrical contact with a dendritic spine (s).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Six young adult (P30) OF-1 mice obtained from the Animal House Facility at the School of Medicine of the University of Castilla-La Mancha were used in immunohistochemical experiments at the light and electron microscopic level.\"\n\n\"The detailed characterization of the polyclonal Girk2 antibody has been described elsewhere (Aguado et al., 2008; Fernández-Alacid et al., 2009).\" PMID:18088366 PMID:19558451" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5020" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

